### Description

When running the `ng serve` command using the `application` builder and having cache enabled, the watcher and the builder do not work properly for linked libraries.

I tried what was suggested in https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/issues/26585#issuecomment-1840982411 and the watcher starts to picking up changes but only if that library is referenced directly and exclusivly in the application code. If the library that we are trying to rebuild is being imported indirectly through another library in the application, it does not work.

For example:
Having library A and library B where A depends on B.
If in the app.component.ts I only import A, changes in B are not picked up.
If I import both libraries at the same time at the app level, the code from library B ends up in the same chunk of the library A and also in the main chunk, and I start getting warnings referring the code [NG0912 ](https://angular.io/errors/NG0912) in the console.

Without cache enabled everything works fine.

### Minimal Reproduction

Setup the environment:
```bash
ng new my-workspace
ng new my-app

cd ./my-workspace
ng generate library lib-a
ng generate library lib-b
```

Edit `lib-a.service.ts` to depend on library B:
```ts
import { Injectable, } from '@angular/core';

import { LibBService } from 'lib-b';

@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root'
})
export class LibAService {
  constructor(public libBService: LibBService) { }
}
```

In two different terminals run each command:
```bash
ng build lib-a --watch
ng build lib-b --watch
```
Install the libraries in the my-app:
```bash
npm install ../my-workspace/dist/lib-a
npm install ../my-workspace/dist/lib-b
```

Go to my-app and edit the `app.component.ts`:
```ts
import { Component, inject } from '@angular/core';
import { RouterOutlet } from '@angular/router';

import { LibAService } from 'lib-a';
import { LibBService } from 'lib-b';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [RouterOutlet],
  templateUrl: './app.component.html',
  styleUrl: './app.component.less'
})
export class AppComponent {
  title = 'my-app';

  libA = inject(LibAService);
  libB = inject(LibBService);
}
```

Edit the `tsconfig.json`:
```json
{
  "compileOnSave": false,
  "compilerOptions": {
    "paths": {
      "my-lib": [
        "./node_modules/my-lib"
      ],
      "my-lib2": [
        "./node_modules/my-lib2"
      ]
    },
....
```

Serve the app
```bash
ng serve
```

Issue 1:
In the console the error [NG0912 ](https://angular.io/errors/NG0912) appears.

Go to my-app and edit the `app.component.ts`:
```ts
import { Component, inject } from '@angular/core';
import { RouterOutlet } from '@angular/router';

import { LibAService } from 'lib-a';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [RouterOutlet],
  templateUrl: './app.component.html',
  styleUrl: './app.component.less'
})
export class AppComponent {
  title = 'my-app';

  libA = inject(LibAService);
}
```
Perform any change in the `my-lib-b.service`

